102.1	Matthew_Barney	Matthew Barney	Matthew Barney (born March 25, 1967) is an American artist who works in sculpture, photography, drawing and film. His early works were sculptural installations combined with performance and video. Between 1994 and 2002 he created the Cremaster Cycle, a series of five films described by Jonathan Jones in The Guardian as "one of the most imaginative and brilliant achievements in the history of avant-garde cinema."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Matthew-Barney-1.jpg/220px-Matthew-Barney-1.jpg
